## 🗓️ Updated Project Plan (9-Week Timeline)

Adding analytics, partial payments, and WhatsApp APIs increases the scope. Here is the adjusted timeline.

### Phase 1: Planning & Design (Weeks 1 - 2)
* **Week 1:** Wireframe the Vendor and Buyer flows. Design the Quick-Add grid and Analytics dashboard. 
* **Week 2:** Setup database architecture (Firebase/Supabase). Map out the schemas for Users, Shops, Transactions, and Limits.

### Phase 2: Core Engine Development (Weeks 3 - 5)
* **Week 3:** Implement OTP Authentication and QR Code generation/scanning. 
* **Week 4:** Build the Vendor POS. Implement the Quick-Add grid and the core transaction ledger (adding/removing items from a specific user's tab).
* **Week 5:** Build the Buyer Dashboard. Implement the real-time sync and the Consumption Tracker visuals.

### Phase 3: Advanced Features & Payments (Weeks 6 - 7)
* **Week 6 (Limits & Payments):** Build the "Set a Limit" logic and warning system. Integrate UPI deep linking for both full and partial payments.
* **Week 7 (Analytics & WhatsApp):** Build the Vendor Analytics screen. Integrate the WhatsApp API to trigger automated weekly messages based on outstanding balances.

### Phase 4: Beta Testing (Week 8)
* **The "One Tapri" Test:** Deploy the PWA. Onboard one local vendor and 5-10 of their regular customers.
* **Monitor & Fix:** Watch for edge cases (e.g., what happens if a partial payment is made right as a new item is added?). Fix UI bugs.

### Phase 5: Launch & Vendor Acquisition (Week 9)
* Push final updates to production.
* Begin marketing directly to shop owners, emphasizing how the app will automatically chase down their dues via WhatsApp so they don't have to have awkward conversations.